Low-hanging fruit

[X] Sound effects — Play short 40k audio stings (mechanicus chimes, vox-crackle) before speaking or on wake. ElevenLabs has a sound generation API; alternatively just bundle a few .wav files.
[X] Daily briefing — On first wake each morning, Omega-7 proactively delivers a Portland weather + top news summary without being asked. Just check wall-clock time and a "briefed today" flag.
[X] Timers & reminders — "Set a reminder in 20 minutes" is a natural fit. Store pending reminders, check them in the idle loop, and speak them when they fire.
[X] Omega7 should monitor his internal temperature and notify the user if his temperature is too high.
[ ] Warhammer Community RSS — Add a warhammer_news tool that scrapes warhammer-community.com so Omega-7 can report on new releases and articles in character.

[ ] Build key phases for certain actions:
-Factory reset
-Changing to a different voice model (by name)
-Loading new game rulesets
-Updating information about the owner
-Reset and remake the various phrases he makes
-Change wake word by verbal request
-Load more wake words



Medium effort

[ ] Proximity trigger — Use an HC-SR04 ultrasonic sensor or PIR module on a GPIO pin. When someone walks into range, Omega-7 wakes and greets them without needing a wake word.
[ ] Vision on demand — The camera module is already there. Add a describe_scene tool that captures a frame, base64-encodes it, and sends it to Claude's vision model. "What do you see, Omega-7?"
[X] Mood/personality state — Track a simple internal state (alert, contemplative, suspicious) that drifts over time and influences word choice in prompts. Idle utterances would feel more varied.
[ ] Validate bluetooth speaker connection skill and behavior
[ ] Find (better) mounting points for mic and camera

[ ] Environmental Auspex: Install secondary sensors to monitor the temperature, humidity, or air quality of your immediate workspace.

[ ] Bambu H2D Telemetry: Use an MQTT client to intercept your Bambu printer's local data stream for progress updates and STC corruption (error) vocal alerts.

[ ] Unraid Network Tap: Connect to your Unraid server via SMB, Nextcloud WebDAV, or the Unraid GraphQL API to monitor system health and data transfers.

[ ] Networked STL Auspex: Program the skull to visually and audibly chime the exact second a new file successfully drops into your Nextcloud STL folder.

[ ] Gestural Soundboard: Program OpenCV to read simple hand gestures to mute the system, play music, or trigger specific litanies.

[ ] Phantom Servo Audio Illusion: Pan mechanical whirring sound effects between your left and right speakers to simulate the skull physically tracking movement across the room.

[ ] Voice Command Override: Implement offline voice recognition to handle rapid, basic system commands without burning API credits.

Bigger projects

[ ] Local LLM fallback — Run Ollama (Llama 3 or Mistral) on the Pi for offline operation. Fall back to it when the Anthropic API is unreachable.
[ ] Home Assistant integration — A control_lights tool that calls the HA REST API. "Dim the living room" fits the 40k theme perfectly ("Reconfigure the lumens of Sector 4, servitor").
[X] Custom ElevenLabs voice — Clone a voice trained specifically to sound like a servo-skull. ElevenLabs' voice design tools can get you a raspy, mechanical 40k tone that Piper can't match.
[ ] Multi-skull network — If you ever build a second skull, a shared MQTT or Redis channel lets them exchange "cogitator dispatches" and respond to each other.